text: Sépeaux-Saint-Romain () is a commune in the Yonne department of central France. The municipality was made on 1 January 2016 by merger of communes of Sépeaux and Saint-Romain-le-Preux.Arrêté préfectoral 8 December 2015 == References == Category:2016 establishments in France Category:Communes in Yonne
title: Sépeaux-Saint-Romain
